<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/a3326b0fe5ca2a562f998bfe3fe28ed6.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 4 and b = 3. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>5.0</li><li>53.1</li><li>36.9</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={4}^{{2}}+{3}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={16}+{9}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={25}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{25}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{5}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{5}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{4}}{{3}}\right)}}}\approx{53.130102354156}\approx{53.1}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{53.130102354156}^{\circ}\approx{36.869897645844}\approx{36.9}</m>.</p>

</solution>
